  "prompt": "Do Jains belong to the OBC category?",
  "response": "In India, the classification of communities into categories such as Scheduled Castes (SC), Scheduled Tribes (ST), and Other Backward Classes (OBC) can vary by state and is influenced by social, economic, and historical factors. Generally, Jains are recognized as a religious minority and are not typically classified under the OBC category at the national level. \n\nHowever, some states may have specific provisions or classifications for certain groups within the Jain community, especially for those who might belong to economically weaker sections. It's important to check the specific policies and classifications of individual states as they can differ significantly.",
